title: Grateful Dead - March 1970 Pirates World (Florida)
description:
Grateful Dead - at the Pirates World amusement park in Dania, Florida. Many famous rock bands and performers played there in the early 1970s and the Dead played two nights, March 22 and 23 according to the ticket.  The show has always been listed on official Grateful Dead playlists as taking place on March 24.

Soundboard recording, frankly tampered with to make one CD without cuts and weird channel drop-outs, etc.  The end result is faithful to the spirit of the event, which was a short, relatively tight set whose length was dictated by the Pirates World people and regulations, or perhaps in part by local ordinances. Who really knows at this late date?

Enjoy this great show. May it "amuse" you.
